review_blob: This is something I have when Im out and about or if I want my fix on Guinness and Im not willing to go out to a pub and get it on tap. Not as good as it is on tap but its still jizz worthy.

So far the best beer Ive had in my quest to find the perfect beer for me. Great, milky head that keeps the full taste of this Irish stout intact with a colour blacker than the blackest black, times infinity.

I think the haters need to chill the fuck out a bit, its not that bad! I find it to have a clean, dry and sweet taste to it that has much more character then most of its low-carb counterparts despite its nothing special look and aroma (Pure Blond Im looking at you!), and besides its good for your figure...

Quite generic, but cheap. I have friends who love or hate this beer, Im indifferent about it. I find this beer to be extremely gassy so I have trouble drinking it for an entire night but looking at the head at an upside-down angle is cool (since its an all clear bottle).
Went on a road trip one time and the only thing I drank was this beer. Has a coffee-like taste and aroma to an overall great black beer.
For a non-stout this packs quite a punch for a beer, Ive only had it in bottles so I cant comment on the look of it. Still tastes good though.
Nice distinctive look with a nice, full head and a full aroma. Has a bitter yet sweet, fruity taste which sets it apart from most Australian beers.
